  "headline": "Occlusion is INTERVENTION-BASED, so unlike the gradient family it does NOT vanish on the position/index output — it recovers the true causal bytes on BOTH the content output AND the position output (the §7 'Succeed/partial — faithful when the perturbation is a valid intervention' prediction). It is the COARSE twin of the §1 oracle (probes occlude→0 only), so corr is high but not 1 vs the full set+occlude+do oracle map. Oracle-as-method positive control corr=1/p@k=1 on every non-degenerate column.",
